TITLE: Creating a Basic Mocha Test File in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: A sample test file demonstrating Mocha's syntax for testing the Array.indexOf() method. Uses Node's assert module for assertions and shows the describe/it pattern for organizing tests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/getting-started.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// test/example.test.js
import { assert } from "node:assert";

describe("Array", function () {
  describe("#indexOf()", function () {
    it("should return -1 when the value is not present", function () {
      assert.equal([1, 2, 3].indexOf(4), -1);
    });
  });
});
```

