TITLE: Implementing TDD Test Structure in JavaScript with Mocha
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the TDD interface in Mocha to structure tests. It shows the usage of suite() for grouping tests, setup() for preparation, and test() for individual test cases. The example tests the indexOf() method of an array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/interfaces/tdd.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
suite("Array", function () {
  setup(function () {
    // ...
  });

  suite("#indexOf()", function () {
    test("should return -1 when not present", function () {
      assert.equal(-1, [1, 2, 3].indexOf(4));
    });
  });
});
```

