TITLE: Defining a Pending Test in Mocha
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a pending test in Mocha by omitting the callback function. The pending test 'should return -1 when the value is not present' will be included in test results and marked as pending rather than failed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/declaring/pending-tests.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
describe("Array", function () {
  describe("#indexOf()", function () {
    // pending test below
    it("should return -1 when the value is not present");
  });
});
```

