TITLE: Basic Mocha Hook Implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the standard hook pattern in Mocha using the BDD interface. Shows the four main hooks: before(), after(), beforeEach(), and afterEach(), each running at different points in the test execution cycle.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/features/hooks.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
describe("hooks", function () {
  before(function () {
    // runs once before the first test in this block
  });

  after(function () {
    // runs once after the last test in this block
  });

  beforeEach(function () {
    // runs before each test in this block
  });

  afterEach(function () {
    // runs after each test in this block
  });

  // test cases
});
```

