TITLE: Configuring Suite-Level Timeouts in Mocha
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to apply a timeout at the suite level which is inherited by all nested tests. The timeout of 500ms is set for the entire suite, affecting all test cases within it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/features/timeouts.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
describe("a suite of tests", function () {
  this.timeout(500);

  it("should take less than 500ms", function (done) {
    setTimeout(done, 300);
  });

  it("should take less than 500ms as well", function (done) {
    setTimeout(done, 250);
  });
});
```

