TITLE: Test Priority with .only() in Mocha
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how test cases with .only() take precedence over suites with .only(). Only the test case with .only() will run, even though its parent suite also has .only().
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/declaring/exclusive-tests.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
describe("Array", function () {
  describe.only("#indexOf()", function () {
    it.only("should return -1 unless present", function () {
      // this test will be run
    });

    it("should return the index when present", function () {
      // this test will not be run
    });
  });
});
```

