TITLE: Creating Conditional Root Hooks with Function Export in Mocha
DESCRIPTION: Example of exporting mochaHooks as a function for conditional hook creation. This implementation creates environment-specific hooks by checking if tests are running in a CI environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/blob/main/docs-next/src/content/docs/features/root-hook-plugins.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// test/hooks.mjs

export const mochaHooks = () => {
  if (process.env.CI) {
    // root hooks object
    return {
      beforeEach: [
        function () {
          // CI-specific beforeEach
        },
        function () {
          // some other CI-specific beforeEach
        },
      ],
    };
  }
  // root hooks object
  return {
    beforeEach() {
      // regular beforeEach
    },
  };
};
```

